OL,6,FAfter a few seconds, a BBC One
OL,7,Fbreakdown slide appeared and remained
OL,8,Fon screen in silence for about a
OL,9,Fminute-and-a-half.
OL,11,FPanorama then resumed ` but from a
OL,12,Fslightly later point than where we
OL,13,Fleft it. This meant the programme
OL,14,Ffinished slightly early, leaving BBC
OL,15,FOne Network filling with a breakdown
OL,16,Fslide again briefly, plus verbal
OL,17,Fapology from the Network announcer.
OL,19,FThe on air fault was the result of
OL,20,Fhuman error at the Red Bee playout
OL,21,Foperation in London.
